 -- Ralf Kaestner <ralf.kaestner@gmail.com>  Mon, 11 Feb 2013 07:59:00 +0100

remake (0.5-132) unstable; urgency=low

  * Increased project version to 0.5
  * Restructured source tree
    + CMake modules now reside under module directory
    + Script distribution under src/bin
  * New features:
    + Changed version format in remake_project() to MAJOR.MINOR.PATH-REV
    + Added ReMakeDistribute modules for automated project distribution
      (currently supports the Debian distribution standards)
    + Added remake_file_permissions() macro
    + Added ReMakePack archive macros for source and binary packaging
    + Added svn2debcl script for converting Subversion logs into the
      Debian changelog format
  * Bugfixes:
    + Fixed minor issue in remake_target_add_command()
  * Other changes:
    + remake_svn_log() has new parameter TARGET
    + remake_project() issues TARGET ${REMAKE_PROJECT_CHANGELOG_TARGET}
      to remake_svn_log()
    + remake_file_write() has new option LINES
    + CMake documentation generator gendocs now distributed with remake
      package and displaying command line help

 -- Ralf Kaestner <ralf.kaestner@gmail.com>  Mon, 11 Feb 2013 07:59:00 +0100

remake (0.4-131) unstable; urgency=low

  * New features:
    + remake_ros_find_package() delivers library directories
    + remake_pack_archive() is a new macros to create binary archives
    + remake_pack_source() and remake_pack_source_archive() are new macros
      for creating source archives

 -- Ralf Kaestner <ralf.kaestner@gmail.com>  Thu, 07 Feb 2013 10:48:42 +0100

remake (0.4-130) unstable; urgency=low

  * Added RemakeROS module:
    + remake_ros() distribution discovery macro
    + remake_ros_find_package() package discovery macro
  * Modifications in RemakeFind module:
    + remake_find_file() sets ${PACKAGE}_PATH instead of ${PACKAGE}_FILE

 -- Ralf Kaestner <ralf.kaestner@gmail.com>  Wed, 30 Jan 2013 17:37:30 +0100

remake (0.4-129) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixes for CMake version 2.8.7:
    + Added module build directory to CMAKE_MODULE_PATH
    + Packages are now created and expected in build directory, due to a
      bug in CPack which ignores the package target directory

